#import "/formatting.typ": *

#recipe(title: "Sourdough Pretzels", panel-width: 12.25em, yield: "10 pretzels", refs: (
  <fob_sourdough-pretzels>,
  <kabc_roll-dough-improver>,
))[
  Batter:
  - 100g sourdough starter #aside[1/2 cup]
  - 240g water #aside[1 cup]
  - 40g honey #aside[2 tbsp.]
  - 12g salt #aside[2 tsp.]
  - 450g all-purpose flour #aside[3 1/4 cups]
  - _(optional)_ 6g Easy Roll Dough Improver#footnote[From:
      https://shop.kingarthurbaking.com/items/easy-roll-dough-improver. I actually haven't
      tried this yet. It should make stretching the dough easier, though.] #aside[2 tsp.]

  Water Bath:
  - 2ℓ water #aside[2.11 quarts]
  - 20g baking soda #aside[1 tbsp.]
  - 15g brown sugar #aside[1 tbsp.]

  Egg Wash:
  // Weight?
  - 1 large egg yolk
  - 14g water #aside[1 tbsp.]
  - Salt, to taste // How much?
  - Sugar, to taste // How much?
  - Cinnamon, to taste // How much?
][
  + MIX batter on low. #pause[10 min.]
  + COVER with solid lid until doubled. #pause[8-12 hr.]
  + DIVIDE into ten pieces.
  + ROLL each piece into preferred shape.
  + COVER dough with solid lid. #pause[1 hr.]
  + LINE baking sheet with parchment paper.
  + PREHEAT oven to 425°F.
  + BOIL water for water bath. Add baking soda, sugar.
  + FOR each pretzel:
    + BOIL for 30 seconds per side.#footnote[I recommend a frying basket, like the one
        I've bought: https://www.amazon.com/dp/B001VZARVK]
    + TRANSFER to baking sheet.
  + BRUSH each pretzel with egg wash.
  + BAKE until goldenbrown. #pause[\~15 min.]
]
